AB  - MacKinnon and Milbourne (1984), in an extended comment on Carr and Darby (1981), claim that money supply shocks do not enter the money demand function for the United States. This reply discusses the economic and econometric errors which led to this conclusion and presents further empirical evidence in support of our approach.
